Overview:

An *AI-driven virtual sensor system* that monitors real car sensor data and *predicts critical parameters* like *oil pressure* and *cabin noise* — even when physical sensors are missing.

When anomalies are detected, it:
•⁠  ⁠Plays a *loud beep* on the laptop
•⁠  ⁠Sends *urgent email alerts*
•⁠  ⁠Logs everything in a database
•⁠  ⁠Updates a *live dashboard*

Perfect for *predictive maintenance, **fleet monitoring, and **hackathon demos*.



Features

| Feature | Description |
|-------|-----------|
| *Virtual Sensors* | AI predicts ⁠ oil_pressure ⁠ & ⁠ noise_index ⁠ from speed, RPM, temp |
| *3-Tier Alerts* | ⁠ NORMAL ⁠ → ⁠ WARNING ⁠ → ⁠ CRITICAL ⁠ |
| *Beep Alert* | 3 loud beeps on *CRITICAL* (Windows) |
| *Email Alerts* | Sent via Gmail SMTP |
| *Live Simulation* | 10 rows processed with 2-sec delay |
| *Full Logging* | All data + alerts saved in ⁠ CarSensorLogs ⁠ |
| *Live Dashboard* | Streamlit UI with real-time logs |



 Tech Stack

•⁠  ⁠*WorqHat* – Workflow, AI, Database, Email
•⁠  ⁠*Python* – Custom beep node
•⁠  ⁠*Streamlit* – Live frontend
•⁠  ⁠*Gmail SMTP* – Alert emails


